fg_segments: Collection of your Personal Information NNPC collects personally identifiable information, such as your e-mail address, name, home or work address or telephone number.
NNPC also collects anonymous demographic information, which is not unique to you, such as your ZIP code, age, gender, preferences, interests and favorites.
There is also information about your computer hardware and software that is automatically collected by NNPC.
This information can include: your IP address, browser type, domain names, access times and referring Web site addresses.
This information is used by NNPC for the operation of the service, to maintain quality of the service, and to provide general statistics regarding use of the NNPC Web site.

Please keep in mind that if you directly disclose personally identifiable information or personally sensitive data through NNPC public message boards, this information may be collected and used by others.
Note: NNPC does not read any of your private online communications.
NNPC encourages you to review the privacy statements of Web sites you choose to link to from NNPC so that you can understand how those Web sites collect, use and share your information.
NNPC is not responsible for the privacy statements or other content on Web sites outside of the NNPC and NNPC family of Web sites.
Use of your Personal Information NNPC collects and uses your personal information to operate the NNPC Web site and deliver the services you have requested.
NNPC also uses your personally identifiable information to inform you of other products or services available from NNPC and its affiliates.
NNPC may also contact you via surveys to conduct research about your opinion of current services or of potential new services that may be offered.
NNPC does not sell, rent or lease its customer lists to third parties.
NNPC may, from time to time, contact you on behalf of external business partners about a particular offering that may be of interest to you.
In those cases, your unique personally identifiable information (e-mail, name, address, telephone number) is not transferred to the third party.
In addition, NNPC may share data with trusted partners to help us perform statistical analysis, send you email or postal mail, provide customer support, or arrange for deliveries.
All such third parties are prohibited from using your personal information except to provide these services to NNPC, and they are required to maintain the confidentiality of your information.
NNPC does not use or disclose sensitive personal information, such as race, religion, or political affiliations, without your explicit consent.
NNPC keeps track of the Web sites and pages our customers visit within NNPC, in order to determine what NNPC services are the most popular.
This data is used to deliver customized content and advertising within NNPC to customers whose behavior indicates that they are interested in a particular subject area.

NNPC Web sites will disclose your personal information, without notice, only if required to do so by law or in the good faith belief that such action is necessary to: (a) conform to the edicts of the law or comply with legal process served on NNPC or the site; (b) protect and defend the rights or property of NNPC; and, (c) act under exigent circumstances to protect the personal safety of users of NNPC, or the public.
Use of Cookies The NNPC Web site use "cookies" to help you personalize your online experience.
A cookie is a text file that is placed on your hard disk by a Web page server.
Cookies cannot be used to run programs or deliver viruses to your computer.
Cookies are uniquely assigned to you, and can only be read by a web server in the domain that issued the cookie to you.
One of the primary purposes of cookies is to provide a convenience feature to save you time.
The purpose of a cookie is to tell the Web server that you have returned to a specific page.
For example, if you personalize NNPC pages, or register with NNPC site or services, a cookie helps NNPC to recall your specific information on subsequent visits.
This simplifies the process of recording your personal information, such as billing addresses, shipping addresses, and so on.
When you return to the same NNPC Web site, the information you previously provided can be retrieved, so you can easily use the NNPC features that you customized.
You have the ability to accept or decline cookies.
Most Web browsers automatically accept cookies, but you can usually modify your browser setting to decline cookies if you prefer.
If you choose to decline cookies, you may not be able to fully experience the interactive features of the NNPC services or Web sites you visit.
Security of your Personal Information NNPC secures your personal information from unauthorized access, use or disclosure.
NNPC secures the personally identifiable information you provide on computer servers in a controlled, secure environment, protected from unauthorized access, use or disclosure.
When personal information (such as a credit card number) is transmitted to other Web sites, it is protected through the use of encryption, such as the Secure Socket Layer (SSL) protocol.
Changes to this Statement NNPC will occasionally update this Statement of Privacy to reflect company and customer feedback.
NNPC encourages you to periodically review this Statement to be informed of how NNPC is protecting your information.
Contact Information NNPC welcomes your comments regarding this Statement of Privacy.
If you believe that NNPC has not adhered to this Statement, please contact NNPC at
NNPC is committed to protecting your privacy and developing technology that gives you the most powerful and safe online experience.

raw_html:
Privacy Statement





Collection of your Personal Information
NNPC collects personally 
identifiable information, such as your e-mail address, name, home or work 
address or telephone number. NNPC also collects anonymous 
demographic information, which is not unique to you, such as your ZIP code, 
age, gender, preferences, interests and favorites.
There is also information about your computer hardware and 
software that is automatically collected by NNPC. This information 
can include: your IP address, browser type, domain names, access times and 
referring Web site addresses. This information is used by NNPC for 
the operation of the service, to maintain quality of the service, and to 
provide general statistics regarding use of the NNPC Web site. 
Please keep in mind that if you directly disclose personally identifiable 
information or personally sensitive data through NNPC public 
message boards, this information may be collected and used by others. Note: 
NNPC does not read any of your private online communications. 
NNPC encourages you to review the privacy statements of Web sites 
you choose to link to from NNPC so that you can understand how 
those Web sites collect, use and share your information. NNPC is 
not responsible for the privacy statements or other content on Web sites 
outside of the NNPC and NNPC family of Web sites.
Use of your Personal Information
NNPC collects and uses your personal 
information to operate the NNPC Web site and deliver the services 
you have requested. NNPC also uses your personally identifiable 
information to inform you of other products or services available from 
NNPC and its affiliates. NNPC may also contact you 
via surveys to conduct research about your opinion of current services or of 
potential new services that may be offered.
NNPC does not sell, 
rent or lease its customer lists to third parties. NNPC may, from 
time to time, contact you on behalf of external business partners about a 
particular offering that may be of interest to you. In those cases, your unique 
personally identifiable information (e-mail, name, address, telephone number) 
is not transferred to the third party. In addition, NNPC may share 
data with trusted partners to help us perform statistical analysis, send you 
email or postal mail, provide customer support, or arrange for deliveries. All 
such third parties are prohibited from using your personal information except 
to provide these services to NNPC, and they are required to 
maintain the confidentiality of your information.
NNPC does not 
use or disclose sensitive personal information, such as race, religion, or 
political affiliations, without your explicit consent.
NNPC keeps 
track of the Web sites and pages our customers visit within NNPC, 
in order to determine what NNPC services are the most popular. 
This data is used to deliver customized content and advertising within 
NNPC to customers whose behavior indicates that they are 
interested in a particular subject area.
NNPC Web sites will 
disclose your personal information, without notice, only if required to do so 
by law or in the good faith belief that such action is necessary to: (a) 
conform to the edicts of the law or comply with legal process served on 
NNPC or the site; (b) protect and defend the rights or property of 
NNPC; and, (c) act under exigent circumstances to protect the 
personal safety of users of NNPC, or the public.
Use of Cookies 
The NNPC Web site use "cookies" to help you personalize your 
online experience. A cookie is a text file that is placed on your hard disk by 
a Web page server. Cookies cannot be used to run programs or deliver viruses to 
your computer. Cookies are uniquely assigned to you, and can only be read by a 
web server in the domain that issued the cookie to you.
One of the primary 
purposes of cookies is to provide a convenience feature to save you time. The 
purpose of a cookie is to tell the Web server that you have returned to a 
specific page. For example, if you personalize NNPC pages, or 
register with NNPC site or services, a cookie helps 
NNPC to recall your specific information on subsequent visits. 
This simplifies the process of recording your personal information, such as 
billing addresses, shipping addresses, and so on. When you return to the same 
NNPC Web site, the information you previously provided can be 
retrieved, so you can easily use the NNPC features that you 
customized.
You have the ability to accept or decline cookies. Most Web 
browsers automatically accept cookies, but you can usually modify your browser 
setting to decline cookies if you prefer. If you choose to decline cookies, you 
may not be able to fully experience the interactive features of the 
NNPC services or Web sites you visit.
Security of your Personal Information
NNPC secures your personal information from 
unauthorized access, use or disclosure. NNPC secures the 
personally identifiable information you provide on computer servers in a 
controlled, secure environment, protected from unauthorized access, use or 
disclosure. When personal information (such as a credit card number) is 
transmitted to other Web sites, it is protected through the use of encryption, 
such as the Secure Socket Layer (SSL) protocol.
Changes to this Statement
NNPC will occasionally update this Statement of Privacy to reflect 
company and customer feedback. NNPC encourages you to periodically 
review this Statement to be informed of how NNPC is protecting 
your information.
Contact Information
NNPC welcomes your comments 
regarding this Statement of Privacy. If you believe that NNPC has 
not adhered to this Statement, please contact NNPC at
